.Dd November 23, 2024
.Dt DNSPEEK 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm dnspeek
.Nd DNS reconnaissance CLI with clear output and safe defaults
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl d Ns | Ns Fl -domain Ar name
.Op Fl r Ns | Ns Fl -range Ar cidr Ns | Ns Ar start-end
.Op Fl t Ns | Ns Fl -type Ar list
.Op Fl n Ns | Ns Fl -ns Ar servers
.Op Fl D Ns | Ns Fl -dict Ar file
.Op Fl T Ns | Ns Fl -threads Ar num
.Op Fl acfikpqsz
.Op Fl w Ns | Ns Fl -timeout Ar seconds
.Op Fl C Ns | Ns Fl -no-color
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
performs DNS reconnaissance with a focus on readable status lines and sensible
defaults. It supports general enumeration, brute forcing, reverse sweeps,
SRV and TLD probes, AXFR attempts, and DNSSEC walks. Results can be colored
unless
.Fl -no-color
is set.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "-threads"
.It Fl d , Fl -domain Ar name
Target domain.
.It Fl r , Fl -range Ar cidr Ns | Ns Ar start-end
CIDR or start-end range for reverse lookups.
.It Fl t , Fl -type Ar list
Scan types:
.Dq std|brt|srv|tld|rvl|axfr|cache|zonewalk .
Default:
.Dq std .
.It Fl n , Fl -ns Ar servers
Comma list of resolvers.
.It Fl D , Fl -dict Ar file
Wordlist for brute forcing (default
.Dq namelist.txt ) .
.It Fl T , Fl -threads Ar num
Concurrent lookups (default 20).
.It Fl acfikpqsz
Bundle short bool flags:
.Dq -a -c -f -i -k -p -q -s -z .
.It Fl p , Fl -tcp
Use TCP for DNS queries.
.It Fl f , Fl -wildcard
Drop wildcard IPs during brute force.
.It Fl i , Fl -ignore
Continue brute forcing when wildcard DNS is present.
.It Fl s , Fl -spf
Reverse SPF ranges during std scans.
.It Fl z , Fl -zone
Attempt DNSSEC NSEC walk during std scans.
.It Fl q , Fl -caa
Include CAA lookups during std scans.
.It Fl c , Fl -cache
Run cache snooping.
.It Fl k , Fl -crt
Include crt.sh scraping during standard scans.
.It Fl a , Fl -axfr
Attempt zone transfer during standard scans.
.It Fl w , Fl -timeout Ar seconds
Per-query seconds (default 5.0).
.It Fl C , Fl -no-color
Disable ANSI colors in output.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "test/snoop.txt"
.It Pa test/namelist.txt
Default brute force wordlist.
.It Pa test/snoop.txt
Names used for cache snooping.
.It Pa test/subdomains-top1mil*.txt
Alternate brute lists.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "DNSPEEK_DATA"
.It Ev DNSPEEK_DATA
Override the directory containing wordlist files.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
dnspeek -d example.com -t std -as
dnspeek -domain example.com -type brt -dict subdomains-top1mil-5000.txt
dnspeek -range 192.0.2.0/29 -type rvl
.Ed
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr drill 1 ,
.Xr dig 1
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Darwin Metropolis
